task.summary: this version reads text out of the mysql database and tries to put it into a local copy of elastic search. the code looks like it should work and it makes the fan spin up and produces no error messages but elasticsearch doesn't get a new index after it runs
this one really works; I didn't put the index name in the index request and also didn't call actionGet() to actually make the request happen
it looks like we are loading the index ok... we ought to run some test queries then try to build an index over in AWS
add simple search client to make sure that searches work on a minimal level
